From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] debug: WR_TRACE printk checkpoints in main()

Boot capture shows main thread logging "Booting..." and "Model:..."
then going silent. With LOG_MODE_DEFERRED enabled, LOG_INF should not
block main. So the hang is somewhere after the Model log but before
"Mount SD card..." would have been logged. Sprinkle printk()
checkpoints (which write directly to console without the log
subsystem) so we can pinpoint exactly where main hangs:
  1_dcdc_done    — after NRF_POWER->DCDCEN0 = 1
  2_qspi_done    — after the QSPI flash device_is_ready / pm_device
                   action block
  3_pre_led_seq  — before boot_led_sequence (3.2 s of LED blinks)
  4_post_led_seq — after boot_led_sequence
  5_pre_mount_sd — immediately before mount_sd_card()
  6_post_mount_sd — immediately after mount_sd_card() returns

This patch is debug-only and should be removed once SD bring-up is
confirmed.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
@@ -146,6 +146,7 @@ int main(void)
     NRF_POWER->DCDCEN = 1;
     NRF_POWER->DCDCEN0 = 1;

+    printk("WR_TRACE: 1_dcdc_done\n");
     LOG_INF("Booting...\n");

     LOG_INF("Model: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_MODEL);
@@ -161,6 +162,7 @@ int main(void)
     } else {
         LOG_ERR("QSPI flash device not ready");
     }
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 2_qspi_done\n");
     LOG_PRINTK("\n");
     LOG_INF("Initializing LEDs...\n");

@@ -171,8 +173,10 @@ int main(void)
         return err;
     }

+    printk("WR_TRACE: 3_pre_led_seq\n");
     // Run the boot LED sequence
     boot_led_sequence();
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 4_post_led_seq\n");

     // Initialize watchdog early to catch any freezes during boot
     err = watchdog_init();
@@ -231,7 +235,9 @@ int main(void)
     LOG_PRINTK("\n");
     LOG_INF("Mount SD card...\n");

+    printk("WR_TRACE: 5_pre_mount_sd\n");
     err = mount_sd_card();
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 6_post_mount_sd err=%d\n", err);
     if (err) {
         /* Bring-up note 2026-04-30: SD card not detected on first
          * hardware cut. Don't kill the boot path - log loudly and
